properties.headline: Gale Watch issued January 25 at 2:49PM PST until January 26 at 10:00PM PST by NWS Portland OR
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 40 kt and seas 9 to 12 feet at 17 seconds
expected. For the Gale Watch, southwest winds 20 to 30 kt with
gusts up to 35 kt and seas 13 to 16 feet at 16 seconds
possible.

* WHERE...Waters from Cape Shoalwater WA to Cascade Head OR from
10 to 60 NM and Waters from Cascade Head to Florence OR from
10 to 60 NM.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 6 PM this evening to 6 AM
PST Sunday. For the Gale Watch, from Sunday afternoon through
Sunday evening.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels and reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 6 PM THIS EVENING TO 6 AM PST SUNDAY... ...GALE WATCH IN EFFECT FROM SUNDAY AFTERNOON THROUGH SUNDAY EVENING
